{"id":21,"date":"2015-06-26T17:28:58","date_gmt":"2015-06-26T22:28:58","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/fuhrlaw.com\/?page_id=21"},"modified":"2022-12-29T16:04:00","modified_gmt":"2022-12-29T22:04:00","slug":"league-city-lawyer-faq","status":"publish","type":"page","link":"https:\/\/fuhrlaw.com\/league-city-lawyer-faq\/","title":{"rendered":"FAQ&#8217;s"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>[vc_row margin_top=&#8221;0&#8243; margin_bottom=&#8221;0&#8243;][vc_column width=&#8221;1\/2&#8243; animation=&#8221;&#8221;][vc_single_image image=&#8221;117&#8243; img_size=&#8221;full&#8221; alignment=&#8221;center&#8221; style=&#8221;vc_box_shadow_border&#8221;][\/vc_column][vc_column width=&#8221;1\/2&#8243; animation=&#8221;&#8221;][vc_column_text]<\/p>\n<h3>Legal Questions?<\/h3>\n<p class=\"page_top_text\"><div class=\"gap\" style=\"line-height: 10px; height: 10px;\"><\/div>\n<p style=\"font-size: 20px;\">Asking the right questions is important when you are faced with important decisions. If you have any legal questions, feel free to browse around the site.<\/p>\n<p style=\"font-size: 20px;\">In this section you will find common questions and answers for each particular area of law that is listed below.<\/p>\n<p style=\"font-size: 20px;\">We will be updating this area in the near future, so if you do not see your particular subject of interest then call us at\u00a0(530)Â 675-4856 for immediate results.<\/p>\n<p class=\"page_top_text\"><div class=\"gap\" style=\"line-height: 10px; height: 10px;\"><\/div>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/fuhrlaw.com\/lawyer-league-city-contact-us\/\" class=\"btn-shortcode dt-btn-m dt-btn default-btn-color default-btn-hover-color default-btn-bg-color default-btn-bg-hover-color\" target=\"_blank\" id=\"dt-btn-1\" rel=\"noopener\"><span>CONTACT US<\/span><\/a>[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_column][\/vc_row][vc_row margin_top=&#8221;0&#8243; margin_bottom=&#8221;0&#8243;][vc_column animation=&#8221;&#8221;][vc_empty_space height=&#8221;40px&#8221;][\/vc_column][\/vc_row][vc_row margin_top=&#8221;0&#8243; margin_bottom=&#8221;0&#8243; bg_type=&#8221;bg_color&#8221; bg_override=&#8221;full&#8221; bg_color_value=&#8221;rgba(119,119,119,0.04)&#8221;][vc_column animation=&#8221;&#8221;][vc_empty_space]<div id=\"ultimate-heading-6588660e0197051bc\" class=\"uvc-heading ult-adjust-bottom-margin ultimate-heading-6588660e0197051bc uvc-5555  uvc-heading-default-font-sizes\" data-hspacer=\"no_spacer\"  data-halign=\"left\" style=\"text-align:left\"><div class=\"uvc-heading-spacer no_spacer\" style=\"top\"><\/div><div class=\"uvc-main-heading ult-responsive\"  data-ultimate-target='.uvc-heading.ultimate-heading-6588660e0197051bc h3'  data-responsive-json-new='{\"font-size\":\"\",\"line-height\":\"\"}' ><h3 style=\"--font-weight:theme;\">Personal Injury and Accidents<\/h3><\/div><\/div>[vc_accordion][vc_accordion_tab title=&#8221;Why do I need a lawyer to represent me in my personal injury claim, such as when dealing with an Insurance company or other parties involved?&#8221;][vc_column_text]<\/p>\n<p>Insurance companies are a business and their goal is to make money just like any other business. Therefore, they will probably not have your best interests in mind. An attorney will make certain that you are compensated fairly for your claim.<\/p>\n<p>[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_accordion_tab][vc_accordion_tab title=&#8221;What damages am I entitled to for a personal injury?&#8221;][vc_column_text]<\/p>\n<p>Under Texas Law you may be entitled to compensation for medical expenses, lost wages, pain and suffering, mental anguish, impairment, disfigurement, lost earning capacity, property damage, diminution of value, loss of use, as well as repair damages depending on your type of case.<\/p>\n<p>[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_accordion_tab][vc_accordion_tab title=&#8221;The Insurance company has offered me some money, should I accept it now?&#8221;][vc_column_text]<\/p>\n<p>In most cases the answer is no. You want to be sure you have completed your treatment and\/or reached maximum medical improvement before you settle your claim. If you settle prematurely, then you run the risk of settling for too little money.<\/p>\n<p>[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_accordion_tab][vc_accordion_tab title=&#8221;I cannot afford to go to the doctor. What should I do?&#8221;][vc_column_text]<\/p>\n<p>In most cases the answer is no. You want to be sure you have completed your treatment and\/or reached maximum medical improvement before you settle your claim. If you settle prematurely, then you run the risk of settling for too little money.<\/p>\n<p>[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_accordion_tab][vc_accordion_tab title=&#8221;What information do I need to pursue my claim?&#8221;][vc_column_text]<\/p>\n<p>Obtain a copy of the police report, towing receipts, property damage estimates, pictures, bills and invoices, and any other documents you think might be relevant. Sometimes it is important to hire an investigator immediately to investigate the scene of an accident while the scene is still in tact. If you have been in an injury accident, you should contact an attorney immediately so this can be arranged.<\/p>\n<p>[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_accordion_tab][\/vc_accordion][vc_empty_space height=&#8221;25px&#8221;]<div id=\"ultimate-heading-3970660e019705203\" class=\"uvc-heading ult-adjust-bottom-margin ultimate-heading-3970660e019705203 uvc-9821  uvc-heading-default-font-sizes\" data-hspacer=\"no_spacer\"  data-halign=\"left\" style=\"text-align:left\"><div class=\"uvc-heading-spacer no_spacer\" style=\"top\"><\/div><div class=\"uvc-main-heading ult-responsive\"  data-ultimate-target='.uvc-heading.ultimate-heading-3970660e019705203 h3'  data-responsive-json-new='{\"font-size\":\"\",\"line-height\":\"\"}' ><h3 style=\"--font-weight:theme;\">Real Estate<\/h3><\/div><\/div>[vc_accordion][vc_accordion_tab title=&#8221;I have been in possession of property but was told that I don&#8217;t have clear title. What do I do?&#8221;][vc_column_text]In order to acquire title to property by adverse possession, a party must prove six elements by preponderance of the evidence:\u00a0 (1) visible appropriation and possession of the property; (2) that is open and notorious; (3) that is peaceable; (4) under a claim of right; (5) that is adverse and hostile to the claim of the owner; and (6) that is consistent and continuous for the duration of the statutory period.[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_accordion_tab][vc_accordion_tab title=&#8221;I jointly own real estate with other heirs or other owners and want to sell but they don&#8217;t want to cooperate. What do I do?&#8221;][vc_column_text]You may need to file a partition suit. Chapter 23 of the Texas Property Code allows one to file suit to force sale or division of the property.[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_accordion_tab][\/vc_accordion][vc_empty_space height=&#8221;25px&#8221;]<div id=\"ultimate-heading-6769660e01970522e\" class=\"uvc-heading ult-adjust-bottom-margin ultimate-heading-6769660e01970522e uvc-4571  uvc-heading-default-font-sizes\" data-hspacer=\"no_spacer\"  data-halign=\"left\" style=\"text-align:left\"><div class=\"uvc-heading-spacer no_spacer\" style=\"top\"><\/div><div class=\"uvc-main-heading ult-responsive\"  data-ultimate-target='.uvc-heading.ultimate-heading-6769660e01970522e h3'  data-responsive-json-new='{\"font-size\":\"\",\"line-height\":\"\"}' ><h3 style=\"--font-weight:theme;\">Corporations\/LLC's\/Businesses<\/h3><\/div><\/div>[vc_accordion][vc_accordion_tab title=&#8221;How can you assist in setting up my corporation or LLC?&#8221;][vc_column_text]We can prepare your articles of formation, simple company agreement, conduct your organizational meeting with all required minutes and resolutions, assist in issuing the shares, and help limit liability. This can usually be done for $800 plus expenses.[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_accordion_tab][vc_accordion_tab title=&#8221;Why do I need an attorney to help set up my company?&#8221;][vc_column_text]Setting up a corporation or limited liability company (LLC) allows you to protect your personal assets from your business liabilities. We can help you set up this entity correctly for about $1,200 in most cases.[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_accordion_tab][vc_accordion_tab title=&#8221;What should I do if I&#8217;m investing in multiple real estate properties?&#8221;][vc_column_text]We recommend setting up a series LLC to protect yourself from personal liability while only having to form one entity. We can help you set one up correctly for $1,000 plus expenses plus a per property deed fee to transfer properties into the LLC.[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_accordion_tab][\/vc_accordion][vc_empty_space height=&#8221;25px&#8221;]<div id=\"ultimate-heading-3820660e019705256\" class=\"uvc-heading ult-adjust-bottom-margin ultimate-heading-3820660e019705256 uvc-9320  uvc-heading-default-font-sizes\" data-hspacer=\"no_spacer\"  data-halign=\"left\" style=\"text-align:left\"><div class=\"uvc-heading-spacer no_spacer\" style=\"top\"><\/div><div class=\"uvc-main-heading ult-responsive\"  data-ultimate-target='.uvc-heading.ultimate-heading-3820660e019705256 h3'  data-responsive-json-new='{\"font-size\":\"\",\"line-height\":\"\"}' ><h3 style=\"--font-weight:theme;\">Wills\/Administration<\/h3><\/div><\/div>[vc_accordion][vc_accordion_tab title=&#8221;When do I need to probate the will of a deceased spouse?&#8221;][vc_column_text]You will need to probate the will in most cases. There is a 4 year time limit, and don&#8217;t assume the property automatically transfers to the surviving spouse upon death, especially if there are children outside the marriage.[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_accordion_tab][vc_accordion_tab title=&#8221;Should I purchase a trust?&#8221;][vc_column_text]Trusts can be expensive and often unnecessary. Usually a well-written will can effectively distribute your estate. However, you should contact us to discuss your specific case.[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_accordion_tab][vc_accordion_tab title=&#8221;How do I prepare a Last Will and Testament with the Fuhr Law Firm?&#8221;][vc_column_text]Call or visit us today, and we can help you get started. We can often finalize your Will within 48 hours at a cost of about $350 per individual or $600 for spouses. Your Will can be less than six pages and still get the job done.[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_accordion_tab][vc_accordion_tab title=&#8221;What happens if my loved one dies with a Will?&#8221;][vc_column_text]We recommend calling us as soon as possible to determine if the Will needs to probated. You have four years to probate, but it&#8217;s best to call us within two months to avoid any potential road bumps in the process.[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_accordion_tab][vc_accordion_tab title=&#8221;What happens if my loved one dies without a will?&#8221;][vc_column_text]If there is a bank account or brokerage account in need of distribution, a Small Estate affidavit may be a good option. Real property can often be distributed with an Heirship Affidavit. If all the heirs at law are in agreement on who should administer the estate, then a Declaration of Heirship Proceeding and an Independent Administration by Consent are good options.[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_accordion_tab][vc_accordion_tab title=&#8221;How do I probate with the Fuhr Law Firm?&#8221;][vc_column_text]Come and talk to us about beginning the probate process when a loved one dies. This can cost as little as $2,500 plus expenses.[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_accordion_tab][vc_accordion_tab title=&#8221;Why do I need an attorney to prepare my Will?&#8221;][vc_column_text]If you incorrectly prepare your own Will, the estate administration can end up being far more stressful and expensive. Letting the Fuhr Law Firm prepare one correctly will save you from the headache of a bad Will.[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_accordion_tab][vc_accordion_tab title=&#8221;What do I do if my parents are deceased and I need to sell their house?&#8221;][vc_column_text]If there are wills, they need to be probated and an executor can be appointed with the authority to sell the house. If there are no wills, heirship affidavits can be used, but all heirs will need to join in on the sale. Similarly, an Independent Administrator can be appointed by all heirs who would have authority to sell the house.[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_accordion_tab][vc_accordion_tab title=&#8221;How often should I update my Last Will and Testament?&#8221;][vc_column_text]There is no required time frame, but we recommend pulling it out every 4-5 years to see if an updates should be made. Then, give us a call and we can amend the Will for you.[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_accordion_tab][\/vc_accordion][vc_empty_space height=&#8221;40px&#8221;][\/vc_column][\/vc_row][vc_row margin_top=&#8221;0&#8243; margin_bottom=&#8221;0&#8243;][vc_column animation=&#8221;&#8221;][vc_empty_space height=&#8221;45px&#8221;]<section class=\"shortcode-action-box box-style-table shortcode-action-bg block-style-widget\"><div class=\"text-big\"><h3>Legal Questions?<\/h3>\n<p><style type=\"text\/css\" data-type=\"the7_shortcodes-inline-css\">.shortcode-single-image-wrap.shortcode-single-image-b5eb8a41f660f0defe443394fbf9852f.enable-bg-rollover .rollover i,\n.shortcode-single-image-wrap.shortcode-single-image-b5eb8a41f660f0defe443394fbf9852f.enable-bg-rollover .rollover-video i {\n  background: -webkit-linear-gradient();\n  background: linear-gradient();\n}\n.shortcode-single-image-wrap.shortcode-single-image-b5eb8a41f660f0defe443394fbf9852f .rollover-icon {\n  font-size: 32px;\n  color: #ffffff;\n  min-width: 44px;\n  min-height: 44px;\n  line-height: 44px;\n  border-radius: 100px;\n  border-style: solid;\n  border-width: 0px;\n}\n.dt-icon-bg-on.shortcode-single-image-wrap.shortcode-single-image-b5eb8a41f660f0defe443394fbf9852f .rollover-icon {\n  background: rgba(255,255,255,0.3);\n  box-shadow: none;\n}\n<\/style><div class=\"shortcode-single-image-wrap shortcode-single-image-b5eb8a41f660f0defe443394fbf9852f alignleft  enable-bg-rollover dt-icon-bg-off\"